50|$|A {{transporter}} wagon, in railway terminology, is a wagon (UIC) or railroad car (US) {{designed to}} carry other railway equipment. Normally, {{it is used}} to transport equipment of a different rail gauge. In most cases, a transporter wagon is a narrower gauge wagon for transporting a <b>wider</b> <b>gauge</b> equipment, allowing freight in a <b>wider</b> <b>gauge</b> wagons to reach destinations on the narrower gauge network without the expense and time of transshipment into a narrower gauge wagons.|$|R
