50|$|This is {{an attempt}} to {{overcome}} one of the primary problems with differing gauge systems - gauge incompatibility. However, it means that the narrower gauge network must be built to a structure gauge large enough to accommodate the loading <b>gauge</b> of the <b>wider</b> <b>gauge</b> equipment, negating one of the cost advantages of a narrower gauge construction. Additionally, a large <b>wider</b> <b>gauge</b> wagon balanced on a narrower gauge transporter wagon is not very stable, and is generally restricted to low speeds of 15 mph or so.|$|R
